  , issueBody =
      Just
        "I'm updating a row with a nested hash literal and I end up with `\"$reql_type$\":  \"LITERAL\" ` in my data, which I believe should never happen. I'm using version 2.3.4. The sequence I'm running in the UI is:\r\n```\r\nr.db(\"crs\").table(\"resources\").delete()\r\n\r\nr.db(\"crs\").table(\"resources\").get(\"raZsCqcfQGTLj7WhpqcquA\").replace(function(var_29) {\r\n  return { id: \"raZsCqcfQGTLj7WhpqcquA\", bag: var_29(\"bag\").default({}).merge(null)}\r\n}, {durability: \"soft\", return_changes:true, non_atomic:true})\r\n\r\nr.db(\"crs\").table(\"resources\").get(\"raZsCqcfQGTLj7WhpqcquA\").update({\r\n  bag: {red: r.literal({colors:{top:\"blu\", bot:\"grn\"}})}\r\n}, {durability: \"soft\", return_changes:true, non_atomic:true})\r\n```\r\nand I end up with the following after the last statement:\r\n```\r\n{\r\n\"changes\": [\r\n{\r\n\"new_val\": {\r\n \"bag\": {\r\n \"red\": {\r\n  \"$reql_type$\":  \"LITERAL\" ,\r\n   \"value\": {\r\n   \"colors\": {\r\n    \"bot\":  \"grn\" ,\r\n    \"top\":  \"blu\"\r\n   }\r\n  }\r\n }\r\n} ,\r\n \"id\":  \"raZsCqcfQGTLj7WhpqcquA\"\r\n} ,\r\n\"old_val\": {\r\n\"bag\": null ,\r\n\"id\":  \"raZsCqcfQGTLj7WhpqcquA\"\r\n}\r\n}\r\n] ,\r\n\"deleted\": 0 ,\r\n\"errors\": 0 ,\r\n\"inserted\": 0 ,\r\n\"replaced\": 1 ,\r\n\"skipped\": 0 ,\r\n\"unchanged\": 0\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nIf I remove the .merge(null) in the 2nd statement it works as expected.\r\nThis may be related to #5977"
